<section id="server" class="pb-3 pb-lg-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center">
                <img class="img-fluid" width="500" src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/icons/server.png")" alt="Server" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2>Server</h2>
                <hr class="border-hr" />
                <p>Many IT teams still rely on manual configurations, custom scripts, golden images or outdated tools to manage Windows infrastructure. This results in errors and slow deployments.</p>
                <p>
                    From a server point of view you need to ensure a consistent, reliable approach without having manual intervention, and allowing you to run the businesses on the software and having to care, water, and feed the servers.
                    When you get to the world of cloud and containers this is only amplified as you are managing the unknown.
                </p>
                <p>Chocolatey provides a standardized approach to server management. From setting up a new server, to ensuring critical updates are in place, or supporting a migration project. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="desktop" class="py-3 py-lg-5 bg-white">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2>Desktops & Endpoints</h2>
                <hr class="border-hr" />
                <p>Deploying software to desktop and endpoint devices is not always easy. Especially in a highly regulated and locked down environments. How do you ensure your teams have the most up to date software deployed to their desktops? </p>
                <p>For endpoint users you have to ensure they are productive, efficient, and have limited vulnerabilities. So how can you ensure they have the latest software,  but at the same time ensure user experience is not compromised.</p>
                <p>Chocolatey provides a unique and very cost effective approach to managing your desktop software. Enabling both a push or pull approach, detailed reporting, and a self-service portal. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center">
                <img class="img-fluid" width="500" src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/icons/desktop.png")" alt="Desktop" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="cloud" class="py-3 py-lg-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center">
                <img class="img-fluid" width="500" src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/icons/cloud.png")" alt="Cloud" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2>Cloud / Containers</h2>
                <hr class="border-hr" />
                <p>Deploying to new environments, whether a cloud instance or using containers comes down to eliminating complexity, inconsistencies, and making it easier to deliver quality software faster.</p>
                <p>How can you begin to easily manage the entire software lifecycle? Treating your deployments and updates as bindependent building blocks ‘packages’ that simplify the complexity.</p>
                <p>Chocolatey offers developers a standardized and repeatable approach to deploying Windows software, in both test/development and production environments. Organizations are using Chocolatey in their Docker, AWS and Azure environments.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="integrations" class="py-3 py-lg-5 bg-white">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2>Integrations</h2>
                <hr class="border-hr" />
                <p>
                    Most organizations have already invested in tools and solutions across their IT environment, so before adding more tools, IT teams need to ensure that the existing investment is maximised.
                    Whilst also ensuring that you are not locked in proprietary technology that does not integrate within your environment.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Chocolatey integrates with leading and emerging technologies. From Deployment & Workflow tools (Puppet, Chef, Ansible, Powershell DSC), repositories (JFrog, Sonatype), pipelines (Jenkins, GitLab, GitHub), and Microsoft tools (SCCM and Intune) 
                    together with the ability to work in most environments, from on-premise to the cloud (Windows Server, Azure, AWS, Docker).
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center">
                <img class="img-fluid" width="500" src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/icons/cogs.png")" alt="Integrations" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>